definitions.definition: The twin villages of Great Thirkleby and Little Thirkleby in Thirkleby High and Low with Osgodby parish, Hambleton district, North Yorkshire , England ( OS grid ref SE4778 ) .
A hamlet centred on Thirkleby Manor in Kirby Grindalythe parish, Ryedale district, North Yorkshire ( OS grid ref SE9268 ) .
